Question: What is the total value of approved insurance policies?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT SUM(value) FROM cases WHERE approved = 1;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN c.approved THEN c.value ELSE 0 END) AS total_value FROM cases c

Question: How many cases were created in January?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cases WHERE EXTRACT(MONTH FROM insurance_creation) = 1;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT COUNT(c.id) FROM cases AS c WHERE EXTRACT(MONTH FROM c.insurance_creation) = 1

Question: Who is the broker with the most assigned cases?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT brocker FROM cases GROUP BY brocker ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT T1.broker FROM cases AS T1 INNER JOIN activity AS T2 ON T1.id = T2.case GROUP BY T1.broker ORDER BY COUNT(T2.id) DESC LIMIT 1

Question: On average, how long does it take for an insurance policy to be approved?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT AVG(EXTRACT(DAY FROM insurance_start - insurance_creation)) FROM cases WHERE approved = 1;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT AVG(CASE WHEN c.approved THEN a.tpt ELSE NULL END) AS avg_time FROM cases c JOIN activity a ON c.id = a.case WHERE c.approved = TRUE

Question: What is the average number of activities per case?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT COUNT(activity.id) / COUNT(DISTINCT cases.id) FROM activity INNER JOIN cases ON activity.case = cases.id;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT COUNT(a.id) / COUNT(c.id) AS avg_activities FROM cases c JOIN activity a ON c.id = a.case

Question: What is the most frequent activity performed in approved cases?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT activity.name FROM activity INNER JOIN cases ON activity.case = cases.id WHERE cases.approved = TRUE GROUP BY activity.name ORDER BY COUNT(activity.id) DESC LIMIT 1;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT a.name FROM activity AS a JOIN cases AS c ON a.case = c.id WHERE c.approved = TRUE GROUP BY a.name ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

Question: What is the total duration of all activities for each case?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT activity.case, SUM(activity.tpt) FROM activity GROUP BY activity.case;
Generated SQL Query: SELECT c."id", SUM(a."tpt") AS "total_duration" FROM cases c JOIN activity a ON c."id" = a."case" GROUP BY c."id";

Question: What is the total value of cases that have at least one recorded activity?
Expected SQL Query: SELECT SUM(cases.value) FROM cases WHERE cases.id IN (SELECT DISTINCT case FROM activity);
Generated SQL Query: SELECT SUM(c.value) FROM cases c JOIN activity a ON c.id = a.case
